S LINE ON DEC 4,1984. SINCE THERE WERE NO RAILROAD EMPLOYEES AND NO RAILROAD EQUIPMENT INVOLVED, THIS NARRATIVE IS SUPPLIED TO CLARIFY INFORMATION ON THE FORM WHICH IS SOMEWHAT INADEQUATE FOR THE SITUATION. THE BOMBARDIER CORP, A FREIGHT CUSTOMER OF THIS RAILROAD IS A MANUFACTURER OF RAILWAY PASSENGER CARS. IN ADDITION TO DELIVERY OF THEIR FINISHED CARS, OUR CREW AND EQUIPMENT ARE OCCASIONALLY CALLED UPON TO SWITCH THEIR CARS FROM ONE PRIVATE SIDING TO ANOTHER AT THE PLANT. ON THE DAY OF THE INCIDENT, INDUSTRY PERSONNEL WERE PERFORMING SUCH A SWITCH WITH THEIR OWN EQUIPMENT AS THEY FREQUENTLY DO. IN THE PROCESS, A NEARLY COMPLETED CAR WAS TEMPORARILY PLACED ON OUR MAIN LINE ON SLOPED GRADE, JUST BEYOND THE INDUSTRY SWITCH. ACCORDING TO BOMBARDIER OFFICIALS, THE WHEELS WERE CHOCKED, BUT DUE TO ICY CONDITIONS, THE CHOCKS DID NOT HOLD THE CAR. IT ROLLED DOWN OUR MAIN LINE UNATTENDED, GAINED SPEED, TRAVELLED APPROX 1.28 MI FROM THE PLANT AND DERAILED IN A WOODED AREA. WACR SUSTAINED MINOR DAMAGE, BUTTHE BOMBARDIER CAR (VALUED AT $1000000) WAS HEAVILY DAMAGED.NoneNoneNone","Joint Track Type":"Main","Joint Track Class":"1","Class Code":"3L","Class":"3L","Joint CD":"1","Incident Key":"WACRWACR001198412","Report Key":"WACRWACR001198412","Reporting Railroad Company Grouping":"Shortline","Reporting Railroad Class":"Class 3","Reporting Railroad SMT Grouping":"SMT-2 - Short Line East","Reporting Parent Railroad Company Code":"WACR","Reporting Parent Railroad Company Name":"WASHINGTON COUNTY RAILROAD CORPORATION","Reporting Railroad Holding Company":"Vermont Rail Systems","Other Railroad Company Grouping":"Shippers","Other Railroad Class":"Class 3","Other Railroad SMT Grouping":"","Other Parent Railroad Company Code":"BBCZ","Other Parent Railroad Company Name":"Bombardier Corp.","Other Railroad Holding Company":"Not Assigned","Maintenance Railroad Company Grouping":"Shortline","Maintenance Railroad Class":"Class 3","Maintenance Railroad SMT Grouping":"SMT-2 - Short Line East","M